{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Pastry","content":["Place butter, flour, icing sugar, salt, egg yolk and water in mixing bowl then mix <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>. Tip out and bring together into a flattened ball, then wrap in cling film and chill in fridge for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl and make custard."]},{"title":"Camomile Custard","content":["Place milk, 100 g sugar and teabags in mixing bowl then heat <b>5 min\/90°C\/\/speed <b>. Set aside for tea to infuse for 20 minutes.","After this time, remove teabags then add eggs, egg yolks, cornflour and remaining 100 g sugar then heat <b>6 min\/90°C\/speed 4<b>. Transfer to a bowl, cover surface with a piece of cling film to prevent a skin forming then allow to cool to room temperature before placing in fridge. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl and prepare pastry shell."]},{"title":"Pastry Shell","content":["Roll out chilled pastry between two pieces of cling film, or on a lightly floured surface, and use to line a rectangular loose bottom fluted tart tin (36 cm x 12 cm). Prick base with a fork then set aside in fridge for 45 minutes.","Towards the end of this time, preheat oven to 160°C. Line pastry shell with baking paper and fill with baking beans then blind bake for 15 minutes (160°C). Remove baking beans and paper then bake for a further 6-8 minutes (160°C) until pastry is golden brown. Set aside on a wire rack and allow to cool."]},{"title":"Topping","content":[" <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place cream in mixing bowl then, without measuring cup, whip <b>until soft peaks form\/speed 3<b>, watching carefully to avoid over-whipping.","Add cooled custard and blend <b>20 sec\/speed 3<b>.","Remove pastry case from tin, place on a serving plate then spoon custard into it. Decorate with fresh blueberries, blackberries and edible flowers (if using), then serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Pastry","content":["120 g unsalted butter, diced (1 cm) then frozen for 30 minutes","180 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","40 g icing sugar","1 pinch fine sea salt","1 egg yolk, from medium egg","3 tsp water"]},{"title":"Camomile Custard","content":["500 g whole milk","200 g caster sugar","3 camomile tea bags","2 medium eggs","4 egg yolks, from medium eggs","50 g cornflour"]},{"title":"Topping","content":["150 g double cream","200 g fresh blueberries","175 g fresh blackberries","edible flowers, for decoration (optional)"]}],"id":"r140386","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-KxA2yHx4xaY\/XZWfY9j731I\/AAAAAAAAfDs\/ZJyRETuSTCkSSaUUJ2zH0W20rynBOAvFwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_u6olIIXUOBBOCLNn.png","title":"Fruit Tart with Camomile Custard","publishedAt":"2017-11-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"8.6 g","fat":"28 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"61 g","calories":"2218 kJ \/ 530 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling film, slotted spoon, rectangular loose bottom fluted tart tin (36 cm x 12 cm), rolling pin, wire rack, baking paper, baking beans, serving plate, refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["This tart is best eaten within a few hours of assembling as the pastry will begin to soften. Prepare up to the end of step 5 ahead of time, then finish topping and assemble the tart when needed.","Make mini tarts using any leftover pastry and custard. Can also be made in individual tartlet tins."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","2h","8 slices"]}